{"parse":{"title":"Seven Myths about Education","pageid":44514834,"revid":806806191,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\"><span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BDaisy+Christodoulou%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.pub=The+Curriculum+Centre%2C+Routledge&amp;rft.pages=133\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Seven_Myths_about_Education.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Seven Myths about Education.png\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/64/Seven_Myths_about_Education.png/220px-Seven_Myths_about_Education.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/64/Seven_Myths_about_Education.png 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"257\" data-file-height=\"387\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Daisy_Christodoulou\" title=\"Daisy Christodoulou\">Daisy Christodoulou</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nEducation</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nThe Curriculum Centre, Routledge</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n2013</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n133</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-415-74681-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-415-74681-6\">978-0-415-74681-6</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Seven Myths about Education</b> is a book about education by <a href=\"/wiki/Daisy_Christodoulou\" title=\"Daisy Christodoulou\">Daisy Christodoulou</a>.  It suggests that <a href=\"/wiki/Declarative_knowledge\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Declarative knowledge\">declarative knowledge</a> such as <a href=\"/wiki/Fact\" title=\"Fact\">facts</a> is being neglected in modern education because of the priority given to <a href=\"/wiki/Procedural_knowledge\" title=\"Procedural knowledge\">procedural knowledge</a> such as <a href=\"/wiki/Skill\" title=\"Skill\">skills</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  It was first published as an e-book by The Curriculum Centre in 2013 and then in hardback and paperback  by <a href=\"/wiki/Routledge\" title=\"Routledge\">Routledge</a> in 2014.\n</p><p>The seven myths are:<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><ol><li>Facts prevent <a href=\"/wiki/Understanding\" title=\"Understanding\">understanding</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Teacher\" title=\"Teacher\">Teacher</a>-led instruction is passive</li>\n<li>The 21st century fundamentally changes everything</li>\n<li>You can always just <a href=\"/wiki/Google_effect\" title=\"Google effect\">look it up</a></li>\n<li>We should teach <a href=\"/wiki/Transferable_skill\" title=\"Transferable skill\">transferable skills</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Project-based_learning\" title=\"Project-based learning\">Projects</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Activity-based_learning\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Activity-based learning\">activities</a> are the best way to learn</li>\n<li>Teaching knowledge is <a href=\"/wiki/Indoctrination\" title=\"Indoctrination\">indoctrination</a>.</li></ol></dd></dl>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Seven_Myths_about_Education&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFDominic_Lawson2014\" class=\"citation\"><a href=\"/wiki/Dominic_Lawson\" title=\"Dominic Lawson\">Dominic Lawson</a> (16 March 2014), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/culture/books/non_fiction/article1385948.ece\">\"Seven Myths About Education by Daisy Christodoulou\"</a>, <i>Sunday Times</i></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Sunday+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Seven+Myths+About+Education+by+Daisy+Christodoulou&amp;rft.date=2014-03-16&amp;rft.au=Dominic+Lawson&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesundaytimes.co.uk%2Fsto%2Fculture%2Fbooks%2Fnon_fiction%2Farticle1385948.ece&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASeven+Myths+about+Education\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-G-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-G_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFPeter_Wilby2014\" class=\"citation\">Peter Wilby (25 November 2014), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/education/2014/nov/25/daisy-christodoulou-seven-myths-education-profile\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>Britain's brightest student' taking aim at teaching's sacred cows\"</a>, <i>The Guardian</i></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=%27Britain%E2%80%99s+brightest+student%E2%80%99+taking+aim+at+teaching%E2%80%99s+sacred+cows&amp;rft.date=2014-11-25&amp;rft.au=Peter+Wilby&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguar